Sentencas: In this work, anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) has been successfully prepared by tape casting and co-sintering technique.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of Ni-SSZ gradient anodes/SSZ electrolyte for anode-supported SOFCs by tape casting and co-sintering technique

Sentencas: The structure contains the thin and dense 10% Sc2O3-stabilized-ZrO2 (SSZ) electrolyte layer and the anode layers with continuous porosity gradient.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of Ni-SSZ gradient anodes/SSZ electrolyte for anode-supported SOFCs by tape casting and co-sintering technique

Sentencas: The decomposition of organic additives and the shrinkage of green tape were analyzed by thermo-gravimetric and differential thermal analyses (TG-DSC) and thermal dilatometry.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of Ni-SSZ gradient anodes/SSZ electrolyte for anode-supported SOFCs by tape casting and co-sintering technique

Sentencas: The microstructure morphologies and the porosity of anodes were examined by SEM and Archimedes method.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of Ni-SSZ gradient anodes/SSZ electrolyte for anode-supported SOFCs by tape casting and co-sintering technique

Sentencas: The obtained anodes with continuous porosity gradient facilitate diffusion of the fuel gas and enlarge electrochemical active three phase boundaries.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of Ni-SSZ gradient anodes/SSZ electrolyte for anode-supported SOFCs by tape casting and co-sintering technique

Sentencas: The open circuit voltage (OCV) was close to 1.1 V.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of Ni-SSZ gradient anodes/SSZ electrolyte for anode-supported SOFCs by tape casting and co-sintering technique

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of single cell with graded Ni-SSZ anode were higher than non-gradient Ni-SSZ anode at 600, 650, 700, 750 and 800 degrees C and were 0.15, 0.30, 0.51, 0.70 and 1.00 W cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of Ni-SSZ gradient anodes/SSZ electrolyte for anode-supported SOFCs by tape casting and co-sintering technique

Sentencas: R-p of cell with graded Ni-SSZ anode was lower than that of non-gradient Ni-SSZ anode.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of Ni-SSZ gradient anodes/SSZ electrolyte for anode-supported SOFCs by tape casting and co-sintering technique
